===Noun===
# From Revelations Chapter 2 verses 6 & 15. An early Christian [[sect]], the nature of which is uncertain. [[Quaere]]: Possibly a belief in clerical marriage and clerical [[concubinage]]? See [[nicholaism]] and the discussion there.
*'''1604''' Reverend Cawdrey ''Table Aleph'': held that a ''''Nicholaitan''' is an [[heretike]], like Nicholas, who held that [[wiues]] should bee commmon to all alike.' 
* '''1611''' St James Bible: Revelations Ch 2: verses 6 & 15. 'But this thou hast, that thou hatest the deeds of the Nicolatians, which also I hate....So hast thou also them that hold to the doctrine of the [[Nicolaitan]]s.
